And include any files or sources

\include{mybestwork.tex}

## How to install

For now there will be no way to install as this is in its earliest form, without any source

<p> This is <strong>WILD</strong>, don't you agree?</p>

-- As you might see, having option to include any markup format in your file might come in handy, especially if you are copying some things from different sources, which are in different formats.
-- It goes even cooler. After you've wrote enough text in `.mx` file you might get tired from inconsistent format. No problem! Just run `:MarksettaConvert md` and *et viola!* your file is converted to what format you've chosen to, with losses due to format shift. If you want to save thing which will be lost by converting to different format use `:MarksettaClean md` and it will convert as much things as it could, omitting stuff that isn't convertible to markdown without style losses.
